# Real-Time Competitor Offer Dashboard
**Bell Canada · Technical Product Manager · 2022 – 2024**

---

## The problem

Bell's competitive pricing team was manually monitoring competitor offers — a process that required hundreds of hours per year and still missed the majority of market activity. The team had no reliable, real-time view of what competitors were offering, which meant pricing decisions were being made on stale or incomplete intelligence.

My diagnosis: **800+ hours per year** of manual competitor monitoring work was producing a fragmented, inconsistent picture of the market.

---

## My role

I led the development of a real-time competitor offer dashboard from identification of the opportunity through to delivery and adoption.

---

## What I built

A real-time competitive intelligence dashboard with 20+ live metrics, powered by recommendation logic and ranking signals.

**Core capabilities:**
- Real-time monitoring of competitor offers across channels
- 20+ metrics tracked simultaneously
- Recommendation and ranking logic to surface the most actionable competitive signals
- Pricing decision support directly embedded in the workflow of the pricing and go-to-market teams

**The specific models that fed this product:**

### Competitor Offer Mention Model
An AI model using NLP to identify keywords mentioned during customer phone calls when a customer referenced a competitor offer. When a customer said, on a live call, "I got a better offer from [competitor]" — the model would pick up the keywords and surface this in real time to the relevant teams.

This gave Bell's pricing team a direct signal from customers about where they were losing competitive battles — not from analyst reports, but from live call data at scale.

### Agent Pitch Model
A model detecting whether or not an agent pitched a retention or upgrade offer during a customer interaction. Used to measure adherence to recommended sales plays and identify coaching opportunities.

### Cancellation Reason Model
Identifies the top reasons customers call to cancel their services, enabling proactive response strategy and informing the win-back and save-back campaign design.

